The paper deals with lossy compression algorithms, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) community. However, the focus of the paper is on the tradeoff between rate, distortion, and perception, which is a problem that is relevant to computer vision (cs.CV), multimedia (cs.MM), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) communities. Therefore, these sub-categories are also likely to be relevant.
